class Solution {
public:
    long long minEnd(int n, int x) {
        long long res = x;
        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            res = (res + 1) | ((x & -x) - 1);
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution iteratively calculates the minimum possible value of the last element by incrementing it and performing a bitwise OR operation with the bitwise NOT of the least significant bit of x. This approach ensures that the result of the bitwise AND operation between all elements of nums is x, and the array is constructed in a way that each element is greater than the previous one.

